In the trial for sexual assaults at the expense of Gerard Depardieu>, the Paris prosecutor has requested for the actor 18 months in prison with three years of probation, with the obligation to undergo psychological treatment, the obligation to compensate for the civil parts and the payment of a fine of 20 thousand euros. The hearing, suspended for lunch break, will resume in the afternoon with the lawyer of Depardieu, Jeremie Assous>, who will intervene for defense.
<h2> Sexual violence and testimonies
"We can blame everyone for everything. But we still have victims in this case confirming their statements. We have someone who changes his version (Gerard Depardieu>). And we have three eyewitnesses of gestures made against Amelie at the crucial moment. This is undeniably a sexual assault," said Attorney Laurent Guy>, the prosecutor, in his introductory remarks. "You will play Gerard Depardieu like any other defendant.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
You are not here to put the French cinema, the media court or the impact of social media under trial," stressed the public ministry, requiring 18 months in prison with the conditional, a 3-year probatory period with obligation of psychological assistance, obligation of compensation of the civilian parties and payment of a fine of 20 thousand euros.
<h2> Depardieu Defense and Testimonials
In the course of the hearings, start Monday, the former sacred monster of French cinema, 76 years old, admitted for the first time to have had physical contacts with one of the plaintiffs, but denied having "diverted to eye" women and rejected every accusation of sexual assault. Depardieu did not fail to criticize the Metoo movement, "which will become terror", according to his words, and feminists. The process was characterized by the particularly hard tones of his legal Jeremie Assous>, which defined "hysterical" the two lawyers of the civil parties. Witnesses in defense of the actor, including his colleague and historic friend Fanny Ardant>, said they had not seen on the set of "Les volets verts" by Jean Becker (2012) behaviors that detect sexual aggression and shocking attitudes. According to Bfmtv, in this process Depardieu risks at most a detention penalty up to five years and a fine of 75 thousand euros.
